[ctns_make id='polyTermDegS1']

    [ctns_front]
Degree of a Term
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:100%;']
The <strong>degree of a term</strong> is the maximum number of variables that appear in that term.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='polyS1']

    [ctns_front]
Polynomial
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:100%;']
A <strong>polynomial</strong> is an algebraic expression that involves only the operations of addition, subtraction, and multiplication of variables.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]

[ctns_make id='polyS2']

    [ctns_front]
Polynomial
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:100%;']
A <strong>polynomial</strong> is an algebraic expression that involves only the addition and subtraction of one or more terms.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]

[ctns_make id='polyDegS1']

    [ctns_front]
Degree of a Polynomial
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:100%;']
The <strong>degree of a polynomial</strong> is the maximum number of variables that appear as factors in any one term.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]

[ctns_make id='monomialS1']

    [ctns_front]
Monomial
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:100%;']
A <strong>monomial</strong> is a polynomial with one term.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]

[ctns_make id='binomialS1']

    [ctns_front]
Binomial
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:100%;']
A <strong>binomial</strong> is a polynomial with two terms.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]

[ctns_make id='trinomialS1']

    [ctns_front]
Trinomial
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:100%;']
A <strong>trinomial</strong> is a polynomial with three terms.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]
